5km from Bu'aale. Almost closed forest with mature trees 30 m high and trunks up to 1.2m diameter. Numerous species including many evergreens, almost no underlayer except seedlings and saplings of the tall forest species. Seasonally flooded area separated from R. Jubba by a somewhat higher levee. A humic forest loam.

500 m N of Gaduud. Well grassed shrubbed bushland with occasional taller trees on fine riverine alluvial sand. Flooded occasionally ( 1 in 6 years) and extensive ponding after rain. Hyphaene thebaica (20m) with many seedlings, Acacia zanzibarica (10m), A. nilotica (4m), Thespesia (2m), Cordia sinensis, Grewia, Phyllanthus somalensis. At least 6 species of grass.
Near Mareerey near Juba R. Isolated tree on edge of sugar plantation.
